===message:<br> It is actually feasible to regulate the migration directly to the shore. Zoning, buy-outs, regulation, taxes, and other things can effectively regulate the growth of the coast.  Later in Against the Tide there are some good ideas. On the other hand, building on the shore and having the houses destroyed by storms or slides creates lots of jobs!
